article.headline: Butler 57, Northwestern 53
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS -- Matt Howard scored 17 points, and Butler defeated Northwestern 57-53 on Wednesday night. Gordon Hayward scored 13 points and Willie Veasley added 10 for the Bulldogs (4-0). Michael Thompson scored 12 points and Craig Moore and Ivan Peljusic added 11 for Northwestern (3-1). Northwestern shot 48 percent from the field and made 8 of 17 3-pointers, but Butler outscored the Wildcats 17-3 from the free-throw line and forced 17 turnovers. Northwestern led 36-27 at halftime, then extended its lead to 11 points in the opening minute of the second half. Butler got back into the game with a 9-0 run. The Bulldogs took their first lead of the second half on a 3-pointer by Hayward with 7:10 to play. Butler led 52-51 in the final minute before Howard made a layup with 30 seconds left, then Hayward made two free throws with 14 seconds left to make it 56-51.
